  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Assistance to Flood-Affected and Displaced People in Uganda</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Uganda has been experiencing a growing impact of climate change in recent years. The country is registering yearly an increasing frequency and intensity of disasters, including droughts, floods, and land/mudslides. The project is designed to provide access to life-saving assistance and protection services to internal displaced persons (IDPs) and most at-risk of COVID-19, floods, and landslide affected communities by providing access to safe and clean water, sanitation, and hygiene support and improving the shelter conditions. Activities under this project include the cleaning and maintenance of water points to improve safe water availability, distribute hygiene and shelter kits to improve the living condition and conduct Risk Communication Social Mobilization and Community Engagements (RCSM-CE).</narrative>
  </description>
